Strand Home Video was the American division for Video Collection International. They were known for distributing the first three seasons of Thomas The Tank Engine and Friends on VHS from 1990 to 1994 and Adventures in Odyssey. The company also distributed other movies and TV programs on VHS, including Ripley's Believe It or Not! (volume 1 to volume 6, 1991), the Sherlock Holmes movies from Burbank Films, Kino's Storytime, The Mouse and the Motorcycle and its sequel, Runaway Ralph, as well as Tina Turner: Girl from Nutbush.
